Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of algorithms for finding the k-th smallest element of a sequence and for sorting a sequence. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms, which is covered by cs.DS. The paper also uses perturbation models and provides lower bounds, which are techniques used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of algorithms in terms of their worst-case and average-case performance, which is a topic covered by cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.CC (computational complexity).
